  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferch","meanings":["German: variant of   Ferg  . Compare   Verch  .","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."]}]},{"name":"Goch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Polish Pawel, Zuzanna, Zygmunt.","North German: habitational name from any of various minor places which get their names from an ancient Germanic element <i>goch</i>, <i>gog</i> ‘marsh, bog, fen’.","Polish: from a pet form of various personal names beginning with <i>Go-</i>, such as <i>Gościsław</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Gotch","meanings":["Welsh: Anglicized form of Welsh <i>coch</i>, <i>goch</i> ‘red(-haired)’; see   Gooch   3.","English (Northamptonshire): variant of   Gooch   1 and 2.","Americanized form of German <b>Götsch</b> (see   Gotsch  )."]}]},{"name":"Margred","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Margaret</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margaret","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]},{"name":"Mared","meanings":["Simplified form of   Marged ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Margred Verch Meurig Goch was born about 1195, in Caio, Carmarthenshire, Wales, her father, Meurig \" Goch\" ap Gruffudd, was 22 and her mother, Sioned Ferch Hywel, was 17. She had at least 1 son with Gwilym ap Maredudd."},"et":{"about 1195–":"umbes 1195–Surnud","1195–Female":"1195–Surnud","1200–Male":"1200–Surnud","1210–Male":"1210–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1174–Male":"1174–Surnud","1211–Male":"1211–Surnud","1175–Male":"1175–Surnud","1180–Female":"1180–Surnud","about 1195":"umbes 1195","1211":"1211","1200":"1200","1210":"1210","1175":"1175","about 1211":"umbes 1211","1174":"1174","1195":"1195","1180":"1180","Gwynfe, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Gwynfe, Carmarthenshire, Wales","Caio, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Caio, Carmarthenshire, Wales"},"fi":{"about 1195–":"noin 1195–Kuollut","1195–Female":"1195–Kuollut","1200–Male":"1200–Kuollut","1210–Male":"1210–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1174–Male":"1174–Kuollut","1211–Male":"1211–Kuollut","1175–Male":"1175–Kuollut","1180–Female":"1180–Kuollut","about 1195":"noin 1195","1211":"1211","1200":"1200","1210":"1210","1175":"1175","about 1211":"noin 1211","1174":"1174","1195":"1195","1180":"1180","Gwynfe, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Gwynfe, Carmarthenshire, Wales","Caio, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Caio, Carmarthenshire, Wales"},"fr":{"about 1195–":"environ 1195–Décédée","1195–Female":"1195–Décédée","1200–Male":"1200–Décédé","1210–Male":"1210–Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","1174–Male":"1174–Décédé","1211–Male":"1211–Décédé","1175–Male":"1175–Décédé","1180–Female":"1180–Décédée","about 1195":"environ 1195","1211":"1211","1200":"1200","1210":"1210","1175":"1175","about 1211":"environ 1211","1174":"1174","1195":"1195","1180":"1180","Gwynfe, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Gwy